name: LaSalleCountyHealth
tweet: Anyone in need of rapid antigen testing needs to call the Health Department to pre-register.

name: LaSalleCountyHealth
tweet: In addition, the LaSalle County Health Department WILL NOT be administering COVID-19 tests on holidays. Testing will resume on Monday, November 29th. Please remember ALL COVID-19 Testing MUST Be Scheduled with the LaSalle County Health Department before arriving on site.

name: LaSalleCountyHealth
tweet: The Health Department’s main number (815-433-3366) will not be manned by staff those days and any messages left will be returned during regular business hours which resume on Monday, November 29th at 8 a.m.

name: LaSalleCountyHealth
tweet: The Health Department will be closed Thurs. November 25th and Fri. November 26th in observance of Thanksgiving.  https://t.co/0uWQCPnPCb

name: LaSalleCountyHealth
tweet: In addition, LaSalle County Health Department offers Pfizer Vaccine for Children on a weekly basis, by appointment only. To schedule an appointment for a child vaccination please visit our website  https://t.co/A2UBSHiNta and click on the “COVID-19 Vaccine Information” icon.

name: LaSalleCountyHealth
tweet: To schedule an appointment for a booster dose vaccination please visit our website  https://t.co/A2UBSHiNta and click on the “COVID-19 Vaccine Information” icon.  There you will find links to schedule an appointment for a booster dose of Moderna, Pfizer, and Johnson & Johnson.

name: LaSalleCountyHealth
tweet: Residents who still need to be vaccinated should call the Health Department at 815-433-3366 to make an appointment.   LaSalle County Health Department offers booster doses on a weekly basis, by appointment only.

name: LaSalleCountyHealth
tweet: The LaSalle County Health Department has COVID -19 vaccine available at the Health Department by appointment only, Monday through Friday.  The Health Department has Johnson and Johnson, Moderna, and Pfizer available.

name: LaSalleCountyHealth
tweet: Vaccination is one of the most important tools we have available to us.  It has never been easier to get vaccinated for COVID-19. There are many options available in our community. To search for vaccine available near you visit  https://t.co/b4RYpX9pLX.

name: LaSalleCountyHealth
tweet: Effective August 30, 2021, all Illinois residents are required to wear masks indoors, regardless of vaccination status.  Masks continue to remain a simple way that everyone can reduce transmission and keep themselves and those around them safe and healthy.

name: LaSalleCountyHealth
tweet: According to the Centers for Disease Control (CDC) Data Tracker ( https://t.co/220jX6ZcSA), LaSalle County is currently experiencing high community transmission based on the 7-day moving average of new cases per 100,000 (223.61 per 100,000) of COVID-19 (Data as of Monday 11/22/21)
